tasks.task_description:
You are a nutrition scientist designing a high-fiber, moderate-sugar fruit salad mix. Follow these steps:
1. Call FruityVice:get_fruit_nutrition with fruit_name="apple". Record the returned family.
2. If the family is "Rosaceae", set your second fruit to "strawberry"; otherwise set it to "pineapple". Call FruityVice:get_fruit_nutrition with that chosen fruit.
3. Examine the sugar content (grams per 100 g) from step 2. If sugar > 5 g, set your third fruit to "orange"; otherwise set it to "banana". Call FruityVice:get_fruit_nutrition with that fruit.
4. You now have nutrition per 100 g for three fruits. Design a 500-calorie fruit salad mix using these three fruits. Your goals:
   • Maximize total dietary fiber.
   • Keep total sugar below 30 g.
   • Provide exact weights (grams) of each fruit in the mix.
5. Calculate and report the final nutritional profile (total calories, total fiber, total sugar) of your proposed mix.

Expected output format:
{
  "selected_fruits": ["fruit1", "fruit2", "fruit3"],
  "nutrition_per_100g": {
    "fruit1": {"calories": X, "fiber": Y, "sugar": Z},
    "fruit2": {…},
    "fruit3": {…}
  },
  "mix_weights_grams": {"fruit1": a, "fruit2": b, "fruit3": c},
  "mix_nutritional_summary": {"total_calories": C, "total_fiber": F, "total_sugar": S}
}
